# Tests that optional fields with label filters enforce their constraints:
# fields not matching the pattern or constraint fail with "field not allowed"
# or bound violations. jobs is the happy path; jobs1, jobs2, jobs3 are faulty.
-- in.cue --
#JobID: =~"^[a-zA-Z]*$"
#Job: {
	name: string
	cmd:  string
}
#Jobs: {
	{[#JobID]: #Job}

	{[=~"Test$"]: name: =~"^test"}// Must work without ...
} @test(eq, {
	[=~"^[a-zA-Z]*$"]: { name: string, cmd:  string }
	[=~"Test$"]:       { name: =~"^test"}
})

jobs1: #Jobs
jobs1: foo1: {} @test(err, code=eval, contains="field not allowed", pos=[0:8])

jobs2: #Jobs
jobs2: fooTest: name: "badName" @test(err, code=eval,
	contains="invalid value", args=["badName", =~"^test"],
	pos=[in.cue:9:22, in.cue:3:8, 0:23])

jobs3: #Jobs
jobs3: [string]: #Job
jobs3: fooTest1: name: "badName" @test(err, code=eval,
	contains="field not allowed", pos=[in.cue:3:2, 0:18])
-- out/errors.txt --
[eval] jobs1.foo1: field not allowed:
    ./in.cue:13:8
[eval] jobs2.fooTest.name: invalid value "badName" (out of bound =~"^test"):
    ./in.cue:9:22
    ./in.cue:3:8
    ./in.cue:16:23
[eval] jobs3.fooTest1: field not allowed:
    ./in.cue:19:8
    ./in.cue:20:8
-- out/todo.txt --
v3 reports fewer positions for jobs1.foo1 (1 vs 5) and jobs3.fooTest1 (2 vs 6).
For instance:
Errors:
 jobs1.foo1: field not allowed:
-    ./in.cue:6:8
-    ./in.cue:7:2
-    ./in.cue:9:2
-    ./in.cue:15:17
     ./in.cue:16:8
jobs3.fooTest1: field not allowed:
-    ./in.cue:6:8
-    ./in.cue:7:2
-    ./in.cue:9:2
-    ./in.cue:21:8
     ./in.cue:22:8
     ./in.cue:23:8
v3 also reports cascading "field not allowed" errors on jobs3.fooTest1.name and
jobs3.fooTest1.cmd; v2 showed those as non-error fields with their original values.
